    overview:`Sits between your application and LLM provider. Every request is tokenized before dispatch — cheap queries go to the budget model, expensive ones hit primary. Dual-validation cross-checks output, catching hallucinations before the user sees them.`,
    snippets:[{file:'sentinel/router.py',code:`<span class="ck">class</span> <span class="cf">TokenRouter</span>:
    <span class="cn">BUDGET_THRESHOLD</span>    = <span class="cn">2048</span>   <span class="cc2"># TODO: tune per use case</span>
    <span class="cn">CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD</span> = <span class="cn">0.82</span>  <span class="cc2"># TODO: set from testing</span>
    <span class="cn">PRIMARY_MODEL</span>  = <span class="cs">"TODO: primary model string"</span>
    <span class="cn">FALLBACK_MODEL</span> = <span class="cs">"TODO: fallback model string"</span>

    <span class="ck">def</span> <span class="cf">route</span>(self, prompt: str) -> str:
        count = self.<span class="cf">estimate_tokens</span>(prompt)
        <span class="ck">return</span> self.PRIMARY_MODEL <span class="ck">if</span> count &lt; self.BUDGET_THRESHOLD \
               <span class="ck">else</span> self.FALLBACK_MODEL`}],
